## Reproducible playbook

1. Clone the repo, install the orchestration tool (`pip install dbt-<adapter>` / `pip install apache-airflow`).
2. Configure warehouse credentials per `profiles.example.yml` → `~/.dbt/profiles.yml` (or equivalent).
3. Set `DBT_TARGET=dev` (or similar) so all commands hit the dev schema.
4. `dbt deps` / `airflow db init`.
5. Run the existing model/DAG once end-to-end on a small partition to verify the environment.
6. Make the change.
7. Run unit tests on fixtures (`pytest`, `dbt test --select <model>`).
8. Materialise the model into the dev schema, diff against a baseline snapshot.
9. Open PR; CI runs the same unit + integration suite.
10. Merge; first prod run is monitored.

